The idea is to keep left and right sum using priority queues(or trees). At every iteration over the 3N array we divide the array on left and right sub-arrays.
Left subarray must be maximized by removing the min element but the right subarray must be minimized by removing the max element. We store intermediate results while iterating from right to left to the array dp.

int removeNElementsIn3NArray(int n, int arr[]) {
        int lsum = 0;
        PriorityQueue<Integer> left = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b) -> Integer.compare(a, b));
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            lsum += arr[i];
            left.offer(arr[i]);
        }
        int rsum = 0;
        PriorityQueue<Integer> right = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b) -> Integer.compare(b, a));
        int[] dp = new int[arr.length];
        for (int i = arr.length - 1; i >= n; i--) {
            rsum += arr[i];
            right.offer(arr[i]);
            if (right.size() > n) {
                rsum -= right.poll();
            }
            dp[i] = rsum;
        }
        int ans = lsum - rsum;
        for (int i = n; i < arr.length - n; i++) {
            lsum += arr[i];
            left.offer(arr[i]);
            lsum -= left.poll();
            ans = Math.max(ans, lsum - dp[i+1]);
        }
        return ans;
    }

Below is the implementation of the above question:

```
class Solution {

    long[] getSuffixMinSum(int[] nums) {
        long[] suffixMinSum = new long[nums.length];
        Arrays.fill(suffixMinSum, 0);
        PriorityQueue<Integer> maxHeap = new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());
        long rightSum = 0, size = (nums.length)/3;
        for(int i = nums.length - 1; i >= size; i--) {
            rightSum += nums[i];
            maxHeap.add(nums[i]);
            if (maxHeap.size() > size) {
                rightSum -= maxHeap.poll();
            }
            if(maxHeap.size() == size) {
                suffixMinSum[i] = rightSum;
            }
        }
        return suffixMinSum;
    }

    long getMaximumDifference(int[] nums, long[] suffixMinSum) {
        long leftSum = 0, size = (nums.length)/3;
        long maximumDifference = Long.MIN_VALUE;
        PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>();
        for(int i = 0; i < nums.length - size; i++) {
            leftSum += nums[i];
            minHeap.add(nums[i]);
            if(minHeap.size() > size) {
                leftSum -= minHeap.poll();
            }
            if(minHeap.size() == size) {
                maximumDifference = Math.max(maximumDifference, leftSum - suffixMinSum[i + 1]);
            }
        }
        return maximumDifference;
    }

    public long maximumDifference(int[] nums) {
        long[] suffixMinSum = getSuffixMinSum(nums);
        return getMaximumDifference(nums, suffixMinSum);
    }
}
